The staff is committed to serving residents with integrity and compassion. Mission Copeland Oaks is a nonprofit retirement community that is open to people of all faiths. They are committed to providing programs and services to help their residents maintain wellness and independence in all aspects of their lives weather that be physical, spiritual and emotional. Moving to Copeland Oaks while still active will increase the chances of remaining self-reliant, healthy and happy for a long time to come.  Campus Copeland Oak’s campus is a 250 acre senior citizen facility located in Northeast Ohio. It is set in a lovely wooded area with walking trails, gazebos, flower gardens and a stocked fishing lake. It is designed to enhance the lifestyle of the residents and to keep them independent and active for as long as possible. Their wellness center consists of an indoor pool, exercise classes and educational programs. If medical attention is required they have an on-site health clinic, assisted living apartments, skilled nursing staff and a rehabilitative therapy is also available. They also have a bank, beauty/barber shop, chapel, library, gift shop, transportation services and 2 restaurants and much more.

Description: Lapham’s Quarterly is a magazine focused on history and ideas.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Lapham’s Quarterly is a magazine focused on history and ideas. Each issue addresses a topic of current interest and concern such as war, religion, money, medicine, nature, and crime. The magazine runs to a length longer than six pages, others no more than six paragraphs. It brings together literary passages with full-color reproductions of paintings and sculpture by the world’s great artists. The connecting of the then with the now is further augmented with the testimony found in the letters, speeches, diaries, and photographs, in five-act plays and three-part songs. Lapham’s Quarterly’s texts are drawn from authors on the order of Aristotle, William Shakespeare, Leo Tolstoy, Mark Twain, Thucydides, Virginia Woolf, Charles Dickens, Edith Wharton, Edward Gibbon, Mahatma Gandhi, Confucius, Honoré de Balzac, Jane Austen, Jorge Luis Borges, Matsuo Bashō, Henry David Thoreau, and Joan Didion. Description: Seconds is a payment system that enables users to complete transactions through web or text messages.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: We believe technology can change the world, but at the same time it can also obstruct us from actually living a peaceful life. The Seconds team holds the perspective that some of the best technology sits in the background of our lives - almost invisible - allowing us to complete tasks with minimal effort and distraction. Great technology solves problems we might not have realized we had.  Ya know, making a transaction doesn’t have to be such a nuisance; in fact it can be quite pleasant. We intend to bring that feeling to the greater world of digital payments. The payment experience should be as quick, simple and intuitive as sending a text message.  The Seconds mobile payment system enables any device holder to send or accept payments, whether through the web, mobile web or a quick text message.   Seconds is uniquely positioned in the mobile payments space by being: PLATFORM AND DEVICE AGNOSTIC. Leveraging SMS and the web for payments allows Seconds to be platform agnostic, meaning any mobile device holder can transact with any merchant or brand connected to the platform.   PROXIMITY AGNOSTIC.  Seconds dissociates proximity from transaction. Unlike NFC or dongle payments, consumers can pay for products or services from anywhere with Seconds. As a result, entirely new categories of mobile transaction--from rental payments to concert ticket purchases--are available anywhere, anytime for anyone.   CONNECTION AND COMMUNICATION ORIENTED.  Seconds sits at the convergence of communication and transaction. Not only does Seconds offer quick and easy payments, but it also provides the opportunity for brands to have a conversation and relationship with their customers via the SMS channel.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Financial Services, Mobile, Payments

Description: 3DFabTech develops, manufactures, and supports technology to create tooling solutions that emulate phase change structures.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: 3DFabTech develops, manufactures, and supports patented and patent-pending technology to create tooling solutions that emulate phase change structures. The company’s products include Re-formable Tooling Systems (RTS), PhaseLok, and 3D copier tooling solutions. RTS creates a tool from a part or pattern at room temperature that can be subsequently hardened for high-temperature use. RTS tools can be used once, many times, or stored indefinitely. When no longer needed they can be returned to a “slurry” state and reformed into new tools. PhaseLok is a family of casting materials to create soluble “wash-out” mandrels, especially suited for high-temperature fabrication of composite structures with trapped features. The company’s 3D Fabrication Technology fabricates tooling and structures of a variety of non-metallics and provides services for advanced composites such as vacuum bag, wet-layup, oven cure,  prepreg, closed-mold, RTM, and more; unreinforced plastics, including epoxy, silicone, and urethane; custom and off-the-shelf syntactic materials; core materials such as foam, honeycomb, non-wovens, and elastomerics; and wash-out and melt-out cores and mandrels.
